This paper deals with data privacy in databases, which is a topic that falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper specifically focuses on privacy in correlated data, which suggests that it may also fall under the categories of databases (cs.DB) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also introduces a new privacy mechanism, which could potentially fall under the category of information theory (cs.IT). Finally, the paper includes experimental evaluations, which suggests that it may also fall under the category of signal processing (cs.SI).
